.:: Puzzle 3x7-Level-2-17::.
7 different games are played: monopoly, domino, snooker, scrabble, canasta, go, backgammon
7 different pets are kept: dog, frog, goldfish, hedgehog, lizard, rat, turtle
The people use 7 different means of transport: boat, quad-bike, scooter, ship, snowmobile, taxi, trike
 1. the person driving the trike is between the person playing domino and the person playing monopoly##2
 2. the person driving the trike is the owner of the frog##1
 3. the owner of the lizard is in the middle##1
 4. the person driving the quad-bike is on the right of the person playing snooker##1
 5. the person playing backgammon is on the left of the person playing domino##1
 6. the owner of the goldfish is on the left of the person playing scrabble##1
 7. the person playing go is on the right of the owner of the hedgehog##1
 8. the person playing scrabble is on the right of the person playing go##1
 9. the owner of the dog is the person driving the snowmobile##1
10. the person driving the ship is on the right of the person playing backgammon##1
11. the person driving the scooter is on the left of the person playing go##1
12. the person playing backgammon is the owner of the lizard##1
13. the person driving the ship is the owner of the rat##1
14. the person playing monopoly is the person driving the boat##1
15. the person driving the scooter is on the left of the person playing go##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1     |      2      |     3      |      4      |    5    |   6    |   7    |
